HEADWORD: Rosetta wood
<hw>Ro*set"ta wood`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>An east Indian wood of a
reddish orange color, handsomely veined with darker marks. It is
occasionally used for cabinetwork.</def> <rj><au>Ure.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

